9 D. When a member begins participation in the Oklahoma Public
10 Employees Deferred Option Plan, the contribution of the employee
11 shall cease. The employer contributions shall continue to be paid
12 in accordance with Section 920 or 920A of this title. Municipal
13 contributions for employees who elect the Oklahoma Public Employees
14 Deferred Option Plan shall be credited equally to the Oklahoma
15 Public Employees Retirement System and to the Oklahoma Public
16 Employees Deferred Option Plan. The monthly retirement benefits
17 that would have been payable had the member elected to cease
18 employment and receive a service retirement shall be paid into the
19 Oklahoma Public Employees Deferred Option Plan account.
20 E. A member who participates in this plan shall be eligible to
21 receive cost of living increases.
22 F. A participant in the Oklahoma Public Employees Deferred
23 Option Plan shall receive, at the option of the participant:
